The paper deals with game theory and network optimization, which are both central topics in computer science. The paper's focus on congestion games and network scenarios suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper's analysis of the existence of pure Nash equilibria and convergence of improvement dynamics suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
